## Access tiers
`private` (never leaves this machine) ┬╖ `team` (your team, via the brain) ┬╖
`{{OUTWARD_TIER}}` (promoted outward). Tag a file's `access:` frontmatter to make
it shareable; untagged and `private` files never sync. Promotion is deliberate.

## Skills & integrations
- **Skills** тЖТ [`.claude/skills/INDEX.md`](.claude/skills/INDEX.md) тАФ the catalog of
  what this workspace can do (harnesses + skills). Skills activate when your request
  matches their description; you can also name one. Regenerate with `npm run gen:catalog`.
- **Integrations** тЖТ [`.claude/INTEGRATIONS.md`](.claude/INTEGRATIONS.md) тАФ connectable
  tools (Slack, Jira, Notion, Linear, GitHub, Gmail, Granola, тАж). To wire one, copy its
  server from `.mcp.example.json` into `.mcp.json`, set the env vars, flip its status in
  `.claude/integrations.json`, and re-run the catalog. Setup notes: `docs/integrations.md`.
- **Share/pull skills** тЖТ push a skill to the brain (`aios push skill <name>`), pull one
  (`aios pull skill <name>`), install it (`aios install-skill <name>`). Pulled skills are
  code тАФ install is deliberate; they never auto-activate.

## Conventions
Governance rules live in `.claude/rules/`. Dynamic-workflow harnesses live in
`.claude/skills/` тАФ run `decision-audit` before a close-out, `scope-creep` before
a scope conversation, `weekly-synthesis` at week boundaries. Synthesis harnesses
are rubric-gated (`.claude/rubrics/`): an independent verifier grades the output
and the harness self-corrects until the rubric passes or its budget is spent.

## Team Brain
If `aios.yaml` has a `brain_url`, this workspace syncs tier-tagged content to the
AIOS Team Brain. Use the `aios-sync` skill (or `aios status|push|pull|query`).
`private`/untagged content never syncs.

